OL,3,CLamb costs soared over last three
OL,4,Cyears due to climate change ` report
OL,6,FThe analysis by Zero Carbon Analytics
OL,7,Ffor the ECIU used Met Office data to
OL,8,Fmodel the impact of the drought and
OL,9,Fextreme heat in 2022, the record-
OL,10,Fbreaking rainfall between October 2023
OL,11,Fand March 2024 and the hottest spring
OL,12,Fand summer on record in the UK last
OL,13,Fyear.
OL,15,FIt combined this with figures from the
OL,16,FAgriculture and Horticulture
OL,17,FDevelopment Board to model the impact
OL,18,Fof extreme weather events on farmgate
OL,19,Fprices.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775178189
OL,3,CLamb costs soared over last three
OL,4,Cyears due to climate change ` report
OL,6,FThe drought in 2022 was found to have
OL,7,Fincreased prices by 11%, the wet
OL,8,Fwinter of 2023/24 by 25% and recent
OL,9,Fdrought by 13%, mainly due to the
OL,10,Fimpact on grass growth.
OL,12,FFarmgate prices, which are assumed to
OL,13,Ffollow through to consumer prices,
OL,14,Fadded an extra #5 (17.5%) to the price
OL,15,Fof a lamb roast at Easter 2024 and #7
OL,16,F(21%) a year later.
OL,18,FJack Cockburn, a sheep farmer from
OL,19,FCeredigion in Wales, said: "Here in
OL,20,FWest Wales, extreme weather is our
OL,21,Fbiggest challenge.
OL,26,@{D@\OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775178189
OL,3,CLamb costs soared over last three
OL,4,Cyears due to climate change ` report
OL,6,F"We've had two very wet winters in a
OL,7,Frow, which has meant poor grass growth
OL,8,Fdue to waterlogged soils and low light
OL,9,Flevels with the very cloudy conditions.
OL,11,F"This has meant lambs going to the
OL,12,Fabattoir at lighter weights and less
OL,13,Fmeat per animal.
OL,15,F"The problems are different for
OL,16,Ffarmers across the country.
OL,18,F"Here in Wales, we're suffering from
OL,19,Fwet weather, whereas in other parts of
OL,20,Fthe UK long, hot dry spells in summer
OL,21,Fare the biggest issue.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUwD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
